dogecoin.text: Did you know? Dogecoin is inflationary! 🔄💸Unlike Bitcoin’s limited supply, Dogecoin’s supply is unlimited. Every minute, 10,000 new DOGE enter circulation, which keeps the price low but also means there’s always a fresh supply of Dogecoin for new users to join the fun.

“To the moon!” 🌝🚀By 2021, Dogecoin had gone mainstream thanks to tweets from none other than @elonmusk. His support, combined with Reddit’s love for the coin, sent it to highs no one ever imagined. Dogecoin reached $0.74 – a huge leap for a “joke” coin!

Doge Invades NASCAR?!🏎️🐶Yes, Dogecoin sponsored NASCAR driver Josh Wise in 2014! A Reddit campaign raised enough DOGE to get his car wrapped in a giant Doge logo. Wise’s car became an instant fan favorite! 🚀 (P.S., Wise even finished 20th in one race).

Early Days: A Generous Community 🥹💚Dogecoin users united to do good! They crowdfunded donations for charities, from supporting Jamaican bobsled teams to funding clean water projects in Kenya. Doge wasn’t about getting rich; it was about giving back.

What if I told you…🐶💸Dogecoin wasn’t created to make anyone rich but as a joke? Back in 2013, two software engineers, Billy Markus & Jackson Palmer, decided the world needed a meme coin. Their inspiration? The legendary Shiba Inu meme: “Doge.”
